    "A3": {
      "text": "Nelson's influence on Popper is well-documented. In the early 1930s, Popper took on the Vienna Circle's idea of demarcation (Abgrenzung) between meaningful and meaningless propositions, with the aim of isolating the propositions of metaphysics from those of science.",
      "label": "premise"
