    "A4": {
      "text": "But just as he began publishing his findings, Julius Kraft induced him to change his account. This change is clearly evident in the first volume's subsequently published eleventh section and the work's second volume. While retaining his notion of the demarcation of metaphysics, Popper now argued that falsification, rather than verification, is the means by which to distinguish meaningful propositions in science.",
